A car crashed into Glasgow Airport, causing chaos as people fled.
British PM Gordon Brown confirmed it was a deliberate attack, raising the security threat level.
The incident was linked to a foiled car bomb plot in London.
Security measures were heightened at airports across the UK.
Two suspects were arrested in connection with the attacks.
The burning car at Glasgow Airport was described as a Jeep Cherokee.
The public was urged to remain vigilant.
The nation was on high alert, with airports closed and armed police deployed.
The situation was tense, with fears of further attacks looming.
